path.aria-label: FACTION EQUIPMENT
RECON SWEEP
Pathfnders are tasked with reconnaissance roles and are skilled at crossing difcult terrain to outfank unsuspecting targets.
Select one killzone edge (excluding your own). Each friendly

g.aria-label: operative that’s wholly within 6" of that edge can immediately perform a free Dash action in an order of your choice, but each that does so must end that move wholly within 6" of a killzone edge (excluding your own).

path.aria-label: SUPPRESSING FIRE
T’au Pathfnders lay down a punishing blizzard of fre, forcing their enemies to take cover and fre back in scattered, desperate bursts.

g.aria-label: Whenever an enemy operative is performing the Shoot action, if the target (the primary target if the weapon has the Blast or Torrent weapon rules) isn’t the closest valid target, your opponent cannot re-roll their attack dice. Ignore friendly

path.aria-label: operatives that have a Conceal order or are obscured when determining this.
Often trained together from youth and bonded by blood ritual, Fire Warrior teams possess an uncanny degree of coordination.
Whenever a friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding DRONE) is shooting or retaliating with a ranged weapon (see Point-Blank Fusillade frefght ploy), if it’s within 3" of another friendly
operative (excluding DRONE), that frst friendly operative’s ranged weapons have the Accurate 1 weapon rule.

path.aria-label: TAKE COVER
Pathfnders are lightly armoured and equipped for mobility. They must use surrounding terrain to their advantage in order to survive.
Whenever an operative is shooting a friendly
operative, if you can retain any cover saves, improve that friendly operative’s Save stat by 1.
A WORTHY CAUSE
Any action that furthers the Greater Good must be undertaken swiftly and without question, no matter how dangerous.
Use this frefght ploy at the start of the Firefght phase. One friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding DRONE) can immediately perform a free mission action.

SUPPORTING FIRE
T’au Pathfnders are expert sharpshooters and can grant covering fre even to allies engaged in close combat.
Use this frefght ploy when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative is performing the Shoot action and you’re selecting a valid target within 6" of it. Having other friendly

path.aria-label: operatives within an enemy operative’s control range doesn’t prevent that enemy operative from being selected.

FIREFIGHT PLOYS
SAVIOUR PROTOCOLS
T’au drones are hard-coded to prioritise the safety of their operators, and will automatically interpose themselves between a T’au warrior and an incoming attack.
Use this frefght ploy when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding DRONE) is selected as the valid target of a Shoot action. Select one friendly

DRONE operative visible to and within 3" of that frst friendly operative to become the valid target instead (even if it wouldn’t normally be valid for this). This ploy has no efect if the ranged weapon has the Blast or Torrent weapon rule.

path.aria-label: POINT-BLANK FUSILLADE
Wielding their ranged weapons with practised skill, Pathfnders are capable of utilising them even at close quarters.
Use this frefght ploy when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding DRONE) is retaliating, if it wasn’t within control range of enemy operatives at the start of that activation/ counteraction. You can use one of its ranged weapons as a melee weapon (excluding a weapon that has the word ‘grenade’ in its name) during that sequence. If you do, you cannot block during that sequence, and the following weapon rules have no efect on its weapons until the end of that sequence: Devastating, Piercing, Torrent.

path.aria-label: TARGET ANALYSIS OPTIC
Advanced optics enhance the efectiveness of markerlights, ensuring the bearer’s shots fnd their mark with unerring accuracy.
Once per turning point, when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding DRONE) is performing the Shoot action and you’re selecting a valid target, you can use this rule. If you do, until the end of that action, if the target has at least one of your Markerlight tokens, it's treated as having one more. If the ranged weapon has the Blast or Torrent weapon rule, only the primary target is afected.

path.aria-label: FACTION EQUIPMENT
ORBITAL SURVEY UPLINK
So efective are the scanning matrices of T’au voidships that they can detect and illuminate a single infantry target, even from orbit.
Once per turning point, when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative performs the Markerlight action, you can use this rule. If you do, you can select one enemy operative in the killzone to gain one of your Markerlight tokens instead (it doesn’t need to be visible). This isn’t cumulative with the High-intensity Markerlight or Analyse rules.

path.aria-label: FACTION EQUIPMENT
HIGH-INTENSITY MARKERLIGHT
This markerlight is exceptionally efective, its beam traceable even through obscuring smoke, debris and soft cover.
Once per turning point, when a friendly

g.aria-label: operative (excluding MV7 MARKER DRONE) performs the Markerlight action, you can use this rule. If you do, the enemy operative you select gains two of your Markerlight tokens (instead of one).

path.aria-label: FACTION EQUIPMENT
PHOTON GRENADE
Upon reaching their destination, photon grenades release bright pulses of multispectrum light that blind and shock those caught in the blast.
Once per turning point, a friendly

g.aria-label: operative that has the Markerlight action on their datacard (excluding DRONE) can perform the following unique action:

path.aria-label: PHOTON GRENADE 1AP

g.aria-label: Select a valid target for this operative and roll one D6: on a 3+, until the end of that operative’s next activation, subtract 2" from its Move stat and it cannot perform the Dash action.

path.aria-label: An operative cannot perform this action while within control range of an enemy operative.
